82/******************************************************************************
83 * EVO channel
84 *****************************************************************************/

86struct nv50_chan {
87 struct nvif_object user;
88 struct nvif_device *device;
89};
90
91static int
92nv50_chan_create(struct nvif_device *device, struct nvif_object *disp,
93 const s32 *oclass, u8 head, void *data, u32 size,
94 struct nv50_chan *chan)
95{
96 struct nvif_sclass *sclass;
97 int ret, i, n;
98
99 chan->device = device;
100
101 ret = n = nvif_object_sclass_get(disp, &sclass);
102 if (ret < 0)
103 return ret;
104
105 while (oclass[0]) {
106 for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
107 if (sclass[i].oclass == oclass[0]) {
108 ret = nvif_object_init(disp, 0, oclass[0],
109 data, size, &chan->user);
110 if (ret == 0) {
111 ret = nvif_object_map(&chan->user);
112 if (ret) {
113 printk(KERN_ERR "%s:%d"
114 ": nvif_object_map, %d\n",
115 __func__, __LINE__, ret);
116 nvif_object_fini(&chan->user);
117 }
118 }
119 nvif_object_sclass_put(&sclass);
120 return ret;
121 }
122 }
123 oclass++;
124 }
125
126 nvif_object_sclass_put(&sclass);
127 return -ENOSYS;
128}
129
130static void
131nv50_chan_destroy(struct nv50_chan *chan)
132{
133 nvif_object_fini(&chan->user);
134}

215/******************************************************************************
216 * DMA EVO channel
217 *****************************************************************************/

219struct nv50_dmac {
220 struct nv50_chan base;
221#ifdef __NetBSD__
222 bus_dma_segment_t dmaseg;
223 bus_dmamap_t dmamap;
224 void *dmakva;
225#endif
226 dma_addr_t handle;
227 u32 *ptr;
228
229 struct nvif_object sync;
230 struct nvif_object vram;
231
232 /* Protects against concurrent pushbuf access to this channel, lock is
233 * grabbed by evo_wait (if the pushbuf reservation is successful) and
234 * dropped again by evo_kick. */
235 struct spinlock lock;
236};
237
238static void
239nv50_dmac_destroy(struct nv50_dmac *dmac, struct nvif_object *disp)
240{
241 struct nvif_device *device = dmac->base.device;
242
243 nvif_object_fini(&dmac->vram);
244 nvif_object_fini(&dmac->sync);
245
246 nv50_chan_destroy(&dmac->base);
247
248 if (dmac->ptr) {
249#ifdef __NetBSD__
250 struct nvkm_device *nvkmdev = nvxx_device(device);
251 const bus_dma_tag_t dmat = nvkmdev->func->dma_tag(nvkmdev);
252
253 bus_dmamap_unload(dmat, dmac->dmamap);
254 bus_dmamem_unmap(dmat, dmac->dmakva, PAGE_SIZE);
255 bus_dmamap_destroy(dmat, dmac->dmamap);
256 bus_dmamem_free(dmat, &dmac->dmaseg, 1);
257 dmac->handle = 0;
258 dmac->ptr = NULL;
259#else
260 struct device *dev = nvxx_device(device)->dev;
261 dma_free_coherent(dev, PAGE_SIZE, dmac->ptr, dmac->handle);
262#endif
263 }
264
265 spin_lock_destroy(&dmac->lock);
266}

268static int
269nv50_dmac_create(struct nvif_device *device, struct nvif_object *disp,
270 const s32 *oclass, u8 head, void *data, u32 size, u64 syncbuf,
271 struct nv50_dmac *dmac)
272{
273 struct nv50_disp_core_channel_dma_v0 *args = data;
274 struct nvif_object pushbuf;
275 int ret;
276
277 spin_lock_init(&dmac->lock);
278
279#ifdef __NetBSD__
280 {
281 struct nvkm_device *nvkm_device = nvxx_device(device);
282 const bus_dma_tag_t dmat = nvkm_device->func->dma_tag(nvkm_device);
283
284 int rsegs;
285
286 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
287 ret = -bus_dmamem_alloc(dmat, PAGE_SIZE, PAGE_SIZE, 0, &dmac->dmaseg,
288 1, &rsegs, BUS_DMA_WAITOK);
289 if (ret)
290 return ret;
291 KASSERT(rsegs == 1);
292 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
293 ret = -bus_dmamap_create(dmat, PAGE_SIZE, 1, PAGE_SIZE, 0,
294 BUS_DMA_WAITOK, &dmac->dmamap);
295 if (ret) {
296 bus_dmamem_free(dmat, &dmac->dmaseg, 1);
297 return ret;
298 }
299 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
300 ret = -bus_dmamem_map(dmat, &dmac->dmaseg, 1, PAGE_SIZE, &dmac->dmakva,
301 BUS_DMA_WAITOK);
302 if (ret) {
303 bus_dmamap_destroy(dmat, dmac->dmamap);
304 bus_dmamem_free(dmat, &dmac->dmaseg, 1);
305 return ret;
306 }
307 ret = -bus_dmamap_load(dmat, dmac->dmamap, dmac->dmakva, PAGE_SIZE,
308 NULL, BUS_DMA_WAITOK);
309 if (ret) {
310 bus_dmamem_unmap(dmat, dmac->dmakva, PAGE_SIZE);
311 bus_dmamap_destroy(dmat, dmac->dmamap);
312 bus_dmamem_free(dmat, &dmac->dmaseg, 1);
313 return ret;
314 }
315
316 dmac->handle = dmac->dmamap->dm_segs[0].ds_addr;
317 dmac->ptr = dmac->dmakva;
318 }
319#else
320 dmac->ptr = dma_alloc_coherent(nvxx_device(device)->dev, PAGE_SIZE,
321 &dmac->handle, GFP_KERNEL);
322 if (!dmac->ptr)
323 return -ENOMEM;
324#endif
325
326 ret = nvif_object_init(&device->object, 0, NV_DMA_FROM_MEMORY,
327 &(struct nv_dma_v0) {
328 .target = NV_DMA_V0_TARGET_PCI_US,
329 .access = NV_DMA_V0_ACCESS_RD,
330 .start = dmac->handle + 0x0000,
331 .limit = dmac->handle + 0x0fff,
332 }, sizeof(struct nv_dma_v0), &pushbuf);
333 if (ret)
334 return ret;
335
336 args->pushbuf = nvif_handle(&pushbuf);
337
338 ret = nv50_chan_create(device, disp, oclass, head, data, size,
339 &dmac->base);
340 nvif_object_fini(&pushbuf);
341 if (ret)
342 return ret;
343
344 ret = nvif_object_init(&dmac->base.user, 0xf0000000, NV_DMA_IN_MEMORY,
345 &(struct nv_dma_v0) {
346 .target = NV_DMA_V0_TARGET_VRAM,
347 .access = NV_DMA_V0_ACCESS_RDWR,
348 .start = syncbuf + 0x0000,
349 .limit = syncbuf + 0x0fff,
350 }, sizeof(struct nv_dma_v0),
351 &dmac->sync);
352 if (ret)
353 return ret;
354
355 ret = nvif_object_init(&dmac->base.user, 0xf0000001, NV_DMA_IN_MEMORY,
356 &(struct nv_dma_v0) {
357 .target = NV_DMA_V0_TARGET_VRAM,
358 .access = NV_DMA_V0_ACCESS_RDWR,
359 .start = 0,
360 .limit = device->info.ram_user - 1,
361 }, sizeof(struct nv_dma_v0),
362 &dmac->vram);
363 if (ret)
364 return ret;
365
366 return ret;
367}

511/******************************************************************************
512 * EVO channel helpers
513 *****************************************************************************/
514static u32 *
515evo_wait(void *evoc, int nr)
516{
517 struct nv50_dmac *dmac = evoc;
518 struct nvif_device *device = dmac->base.device;
519 u32 put = nvif_rd32(&dmac->base.user, 0x0000) / 4;
520
521 spin_lock(&dmac->lock);
522 if (put + nr >= (PAGE_SIZE / 4) - 8) {
523 dmac->ptr[put] = 0x20000000;
524
525 nvif_wr32(&dmac->base.user, 0x0000, 0x00000000);
526 if (nvif_msec(device, 2000,
527 if (!nvif_rd32(&dmac->base.user, 0x0004))
528 break;
529 ) < 0) {
530 spin_unlock(&dmac->lock);
531 printk(KERN_ERR "nouveau: evo channel stalled\n");
532 return NULL;
533 }
534
535 put = 0;
536 }
537
538 return dmac->ptr + put;
539}
540
541static void
542evo_kick(u32 *push, void *evoc)
543{
544 struct nv50_dmac *dmac = evoc;
545 nvif_wr32(&dmac->base.user, 0x0000, (push - dmac->ptr) << 2);
546 spin_unlock(&dmac->lock);
547}
548
549#if 1
550#define evo_mthd(p,m,s) *((p)++) = (((s) << 18) | (m))
551#define evo_data(p,d) *((p)++) = (d)
552#else
553#define evo_mthd(p,m,s) do { \
554 const u32 _m = (m), _s = (s); \
555 printk(KERN_ERR "%04x %d %s\n", _m, _s, __func__); \
556 *((p)++) = ((_s << 18) | _m); \
557} while(0)
558#define evo_data(p,d) do { \
559 const u32 _d = (d); \
560 printk(KERN_ERR "\t%08x\n", _d); \
561 *((p)++) = _d; \
562} while(0)
563#endif
564
565static bool
566evo_sync_wait(void *data)
567{
568 if (nouveau_bo_rd32(data, EVO_MAST_NTFY) != 0x00000000)
569 return true;
570 usleep_range(1, 2);
571 return false;
572}
573
574static int
575evo_sync(struct drm_device *dev)
576{
577 struct nvif_device *device = &nouveau_drm(dev)->device;
578 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(dev);
579 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(dev);
580 u32 *push = evo_wait(mast, 8);
581 if (push) {
582 nouveau_bo_wr32(disp->sync, EVO_MAST_NTFY, 0x00000000);
583 evo_mthd(push, 0x0084, 1);
584 evo_data(push, 0x80000000 | EVO_MAST_NTFY);
585 evo_mthd(push, 0x0080, 2);
586 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
587 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
588 evo_kick(push, mast);
589 if (nvif_msec(device, 2000,
590 if (evo_sync_wait(disp->sync))
591 break;
592 ) >= 0)
593 return 0;
594 }
595
596 return -EBUSY;
597}

608struct nv50_display_flip {
609 struct nv50_disp *disp;
610 struct nv50_sync *chan;
611};

613static bool
614nv50_display_flip_wait(void *data)
615{
616 struct nv50_display_flip *flip = data;
617 if (nouveau_bo_rd32(flip->disp->sync, flip->chan->addr / 4) ==
618 flip->chan->data)
619 return true;
620 usleep_range(1, 2);
621 return false;
622}

624void
625nv50_display_flip_stop(struct drm_crtc *crtc)
626{
627 struct nvif_device *device = &nouveau_drm(crtc->dev)->device;
628 struct nv50_display_flip flip = {
629 .disp = nv50_disp(crtc->dev),
630 .chan = nv50_sync(crtc),
631 };
632 u32 *push;
633
634 push = evo_wait(flip.chan, 8);
635 if (push) {
636 evo_mthd(push, 0x0084, 1);
637 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
638 evo_mthd(push, 0x0094, 1);
639 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
640 evo_mthd(push, 0x00c0, 1);
641 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
642 evo_mthd(push, 0x0080, 1);
643 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
644 evo_kick(push, flip.chan);
645 }
646
647 nvif_msec(device, 2000,
648 if (nv50_display_flip_wait(&flip))
649 break;
650 );
651}

653int
654nv50_display_flip_next(struct drm_crtc *crtc, struct drm_framebuffer *fb,
655 struct nouveau_channel *chan, u32 swap_interval)
656{
657 struct nouveau_framebuffer *nv_fb = nouveau_framebuffer(fb);
658 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(crtc);
659 struct nv50_head *head = nv50_head(crtc);
660 struct nv50_sync *sync = nv50_sync(crtc);
661 u32 *push;
662 int ret;
663
664 if (crtc->primary->fb->width != fb->width ||
665 crtc->primary->fb->height != fb->height)
666 return -EINVAL;
667
668 swap_interval <<= 4;
669 if (swap_interval == 0)
670 swap_interval |= 0x100;
671 if (chan == NULL)
672 evo_sync(crtc->dev);
673
674 push = evo_wait(sync, 128);
675 if (unlikely(push == NULL))
676 return -EBUSY;
677
678 if (chan && chan->user.oclass < G82_CHANNEL_GPFIFO) {
679 ret = RING_SPACE(chan, 8);
680 if (ret)
681 return ret;
682
683 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV11_SUBCHAN_DMA_SEMAPHORE, 2);
684 OUT_RING (chan, NvEvoSema0 + nv_crtc->index);
685 OUT_RING (chan, sync->addr ^ 0x10);
686 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV11_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_RELEASE, 1);
687 OUT_RING (chan, sync->data + 1);
688 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV11_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_OFFSET, 2);
689 OUT_RING (chan, sync->addr);
690 OUT_RING (chan, sync->data);
691 } else
692 if (chan && chan->user.oclass < FERMI_CHANNEL_GPFIFO) {
693 u64 addr = nv84_fence_crtc(chan, nv_crtc->index) + sync->addr;
694 ret = RING_SPACE(chan, 12);
695 if (ret)
696 return ret;
697
698 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV11_SUBCHAN_DMA_SEMAPHORE, 1);
699 OUT_RING (chan, chan->vram.handle);
700 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_ADDRESS_HIGH, 4);
701 OUT_RING (chan, upper_32_bits(addr ^ 0x10));
702 OUT_RING (chan, lower_32_bits(addr ^ 0x10));
703 OUT_RING (chan, sync->data + 1);
704 OUT_RING (chan, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_TRIGGER_WRITE_LONG);
705 BEGIN_NV04(chan, 0, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_ADDRESS_HIGH, 4);
706 OUT_RING (chan, upper_32_bits(addr));
707 OUT_RING (chan, lower_32_bits(addr));
708 OUT_RING (chan, sync->data);
709 OUT_RING (chan, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_TRIGGER_ACQUIRE_EQUAL);
710 } else
711 if (chan) {
712 u64 addr = nv84_fence_crtc(chan, nv_crtc->index) + sync->addr;
713 ret = RING_SPACE(chan, 10);
714 if (ret)
715 return ret;
716
717 BEGIN_NVC0(chan, 0, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_ADDRESS_HIGH, 4);
718 OUT_RING (chan, upper_32_bits(addr ^ 0x10));
719 OUT_RING (chan, lower_32_bits(addr ^ 0x10));
720 OUT_RING (chan, sync->data + 1);
721 OUT_RING (chan, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_TRIGGER_WRITE_LONG |
722 NVC0_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_TRIGGER_YIELD);
723 BEGIN_NVC0(chan, 0, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_ADDRESS_HIGH, 4);
724 OUT_RING (chan, upper_32_bits(addr));
725 OUT_RING (chan, lower_32_bits(addr));
726 OUT_RING (chan, sync->data);
727 OUT_RING (chan, NV84_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_TRIGGER_ACQUIRE_EQUAL |
728 NVC0_SUBCHAN_SEMAPHORE_TRIGGER_YIELD);
729 }
730
731 if (chan) {
732 sync->addr ^= 0x10;
733 sync->data++;
734 FIRE_RING (chan);
735 }
736
737 /* queue the flip */
738 evo_mthd(push, 0x0100, 1);
739 evo_data(push, 0xfffe0000);
740 evo_mthd(push, 0x0084, 1);
741 evo_data(push, swap_interval);
742 if (!(swap_interval & 0x00000100)) {
743 evo_mthd(push, 0x00e0, 1);
744 evo_data(push, 0x40000000);
745 }
746 evo_mthd(push, 0x0088, 4);
747 evo_data(push, sync->addr);
748 evo_data(push, sync->data++);
749 evo_data(push, sync->data);
750 evo_data(push, sync->base.sync.handle);
751 evo_mthd(push, 0x00a0, 2);
752 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
753 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
754 evo_mthd(push, 0x00c0, 1);
755 evo_data(push, nv_fb->r_handle);
756 evo_mthd(push, 0x0110, 2);
757 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
758 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
759 if (nv50_vers(sync) < GF110_DISP_BASE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
760 evo_mthd(push, 0x0800, 5);
761 evo_data(push, nv_fb->nvbo->bo.offset >> 8);
762 evo_data(push, 0);
763 evo_data(push, (fb->height << 16) | fb->width);
764 evo_data(push, nv_fb->r_pitch);
765 evo_data(push, nv_fb->r_format);
766 } else {
767 evo_mthd(push, 0x0400, 5);
768 evo_data(push, nv_fb->nvbo->bo.offset >> 8);
769 evo_data(push, 0);
770 evo_data(push, (fb->height << 16) | fb->width);
771 evo_data(push, nv_fb->r_pitch);
772 evo_data(push, nv_fb->r_format);
773 }
774 evo_mthd(push, 0x0080, 1);
775 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
776 evo_kick(push, sync);
777
778 nouveau_bo_ref(nv_fb->nvbo, &head->image);
779 return 0;
780}

783 * CRTC
784 *****************************************************************************/
785static int
786nv50_crtc_set_dither(struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc, bool update)
787{
788 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(nv_crtc->base.dev);
789 struct nouveau_connector *nv_connector;
790 struct drm_connector *connector;
791 u32 *push, mode = 0x00;
792
793 nv_connector = nouveau_crtc_connector_get(nv_crtc);
794 connector = &nv_connector->base;
795 if (nv_connector->dithering_mode == DITHERING_MODE_AUTO) {
796 if (nv_crtc->base.primary->fb->depth > connector->display_info.bpc * 3)
797 mode = DITHERING_MODE_DYNAMIC2X2;
798 } else {
799 mode = nv_connector->dithering_mode;
800 }
801
802 if (nv_connector->dithering_depth == DITHERING_DEPTH_AUTO) {
803 if (connector->display_info.bpc >= 8)
804 mode |= DITHERING_DEPTH_8BPC;
805 } else {
806 mode |= nv_connector->dithering_depth;
807 }
808
809 push = evo_wait(mast, 4);
810 if (push) {
811 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
812 evo_mthd(push, 0x08a0 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x0400), 1);
813 evo_data(push, mode);
814 } else
815 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GK104_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
816 evo_mthd(push, 0x0490 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x0300), 1);
817 evo_data(push, mode);
818 } else {
819 evo_mthd(push, 0x04a0 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x0300), 1);
820 evo_data(push, mode);
821 }
822
823 if (update) {
824 evo_mthd(push, 0x0080, 1);
825 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
826 }
827 evo_kick(push, mast);
828 }
829
830 return 0;
831}

833static int
834nv50_crtc_set_scale(struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc, bool update)
835{
836 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(nv_crtc->base.dev);
837 struct drm_display_mode *omode, *umode = &nv_crtc->base.mode;
838 struct drm_crtc *crtc = &nv_crtc->base;
839 struct nouveau_connector *nv_connector;
840 int mode = DRM_MODE_SCALE_NONE;
841 u32 oX, oY, *push;
842
843 /* start off at the resolution we programmed the crtc for, this
844 * effectively handles NONE/FULL scaling
845 */
846 nv_connector = nouveau_crtc_connector_get(nv_crtc);
847 if (nv_connector && nv_connector->native_mode) {
848 mode = nv_connector->scaling_mode;
849 if (nv_connector->scaling_full) /* non-EDID LVDS/eDP mode */
850 mode = DRM_MODE_SCALE_FULLSCREEN;
851 }
852
853 if (mode != DRM_MODE_SCALE_NONE)
854 omode = nv_connector->native_mode;
855 else
856 omode = umode;
857
858 oX = omode->hdisplay;
859 oY = omode->vdisplay;
860 if (omode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_DBLSCAN)
861 oY *= 2;
862
863 /* add overscan compensation if necessary, will keep the aspect
864 * ratio the same as the backend mode unless overridden by the
865 * user setting both hborder and vborder properties.
866 */
867 if (nv_connector && ( nv_connector->underscan == UNDERSCAN_ON ||
868 (nv_connector->underscan == UNDERSCAN_AUTO &&
869 nv_connector->edid &&
870 drm_detect_hdmi_monitor(nv_connector->edid)))) {
871 u32 bX = nv_connector->underscan_hborder;
872 u32 bY = nv_connector->underscan_vborder;
873 u32 aspect = (oY << 19) / oX;
874
875 if (bX) {
876 oX -= (bX * 2);
877 if (bY) oY -= (bY * 2);
878 else oY = ((oX * aspect) + (aspect / 2)) >> 19;
879 } else {
880 oX -= (oX >> 4) + 32;
881 if (bY) oY -= (bY * 2);
882 else oY = ((oX * aspect) + (aspect / 2)) >> 19;
883 }
884 }
885
886 /* handle CENTER/ASPECT scaling, taking into account the areas
887 * removed already for overscan compensation
888 */
889 switch (mode) {
890 case DRM_MODE_SCALE_CENTER:
891 oX = min((u32)umode->hdisplay, oX);
892 oY = min((u32)umode->vdisplay, oY);
893 /* fall-through */
894 case DRM_MODE_SCALE_ASPECT:
895 if (oY < oX) {
896 u32 aspect = (umode->hdisplay << 19) / umode->vdisplay;
897 oX = ((oY * aspect) + (aspect / 2)) >> 19;
898 } else {
899 u32 aspect = (umode->vdisplay << 19) / umode->hdisplay;
900 oY = ((oX * aspect) + (aspect / 2)) >> 19;
901 }
902 break;
903 default:
904 break;
905 }
906
907 push = evo_wait(mast, 8);
908 if (push) {
909 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
910 /*XXX: SCALE_CTRL_ACTIVE??? */
911 evo_mthd(push, 0x08d8 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 2);
912 evo_data(push, (oY << 16) | oX);
913 evo_data(push, (oY << 16) | oX);
914 evo_mthd(push, 0x08a4 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
915 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
916 evo_mthd(push, 0x08c8 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
917 evo_data(push, umode->vdisplay << 16 | umode->hdisplay);
918 } else {
919 evo_mthd(push, 0x04c0 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 3);
920 evo_data(push, (oY << 16) | oX);
921 evo_data(push, (oY << 16) | oX);
922 evo_data(push, (oY << 16) | oX);
923 evo_mthd(push, 0x0494 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
924 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
925 evo_mthd(push, 0x04b8 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
926 evo_data(push, umode->vdisplay << 16 | umode->hdisplay);
927 }
928
929 evo_kick(push, mast);
930
931 if (update) {
932 nv50_display_flip_stop(crtc);
933 nv50_display_flip_next(crtc, crtc->primary->fb,
934 NULL, 1);
935 }
936 }
937
938 return 0;
939}

957static int
958nv50_crtc_set_color_vibrance(struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc, bool update)
959{
960 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(nv_crtc->base.dev);
961 u32 *push, hue, vib;
962 int adj;
963
964 adj = (nv_crtc->color_vibrance > 0) ? 50 : 0;
965 vib = ((nv_crtc->color_vibrance * 2047 + adj) / 100) & 0xfff;
966 hue = ((nv_crtc->vibrant_hue * 2047) / 100) & 0xfff;
967
968 push = evo_wait(mast, 16);
969 if (push) {
970 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
971 evo_mthd(push, 0x08a8 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
972 evo_data(push, (hue << 20) | (vib << 8));
973 } else {
974 evo_mthd(push, 0x0498 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
975 evo_data(push, (hue << 20) | (vib << 8));
976 }
977
978 if (update) {
979 evo_mthd(push, 0x0080, 1);
980 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
981 }
982 evo_kick(push, mast);
983 }
984
985 return 0;

988static int
989nv50_crtc_set_image(struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc, struct drm_framebuffer *fb,
990 int x, int y, bool update)
991{
992 struct nouveau_framebuffer *nvfb = nouveau_framebuffer(fb);
993 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(nv_crtc->base.dev);
994 u32 *push;
995
996 push = evo_wait(mast, 16);
997 if (push) {
998 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
999 evo_mthd(push, 0x0860 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
1000 evo_data(push, nvfb->nvbo->bo.offset >> 8);
1001 evo_mthd(push, 0x0868 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 3);
1002 evo_data(push, (fb->height << 16) | fb->width);
1003 evo_data(push, nvfb->r_pitch);
1004 evo_data(push, nvfb->r_format);
1005 evo_mthd(push, 0x08c0 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
1006 evo_data(push, (y << 16) | x);
1007 if (nv50_vers(mast) > NV50_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
1008 evo_mthd(push, 0x0874 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
1009 evo_data(push, nvfb->r_handle);
1010 }
1011 } else {
1012 evo_mthd(push, 0x0460 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
1013 evo_data(push, nvfb->nvbo->bo.offset >> 8);
1014 evo_mthd(push, 0x0468 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 4);
1015 evo_data(push, (fb->height << 16) | fb->width);
1016 evo_data(push, nvfb->r_pitch);
1017 evo_data(push, nvfb->r_format);
1018 evo_data(push, nvfb->r_handle);
1019 evo_mthd(push, 0x04b0 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
1020 evo_data(push, (y << 16) | x);
1021 }
1022
1023 if (update) {
1024 evo_mthd(push, 0x0080, 1);
1025 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
1026 }
1027 evo_kick(push, mast);
1028 }
1029
1030 nv_crtc->fb.handle = nvfb->r_handle;
1031 return 0;

1135 evo_data(push, 0x40000000);

1137 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);

1139 evo_mthd(push, 0x0474 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
1140 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
1141 evo_mthd(push, 0x0440 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
1142 evo_data(push, 0x03000000);

1153static void
1154nv50_crtc_commit(struct drm_crtc *crtc)
1155{
1156 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(crtc);
1157 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(crtc->dev);
1158 u32 *push;
1159
1160 push = evo_wait(mast, 32);
1161 if (push) {
1162 if (nv50_vers(mast) < G82_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
1163 evo_mthd(push, 0x0874 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
1164 evo_data(push, nv_crtc->fb.handle);
1165 evo_mthd(push, 0x0840 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 2);
1166 evo_data(push, 0xc0000000);
1167 evo_data(push, nv_crtc->lut.nvbo->bo.offset >> 8);
1168 } else
1169 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
1170 evo_mthd(push, 0x0874 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
1171 evo_data(push, nv_crtc->fb.handle);
1172 evo_mthd(push, 0x0840 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 2);
1173 evo_data(push, 0xc0000000);
1174 evo_data(push, nv_crtc->lut.nvbo->bo.offset >> 8);
1175 evo_mthd(push, 0x085c + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
1176 evo_data(push, mast->base.vram.handle);
1177 } else {
1178 evo_mthd(push, 0x0474 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
1179 evo_data(push, nv_crtc->fb.handle);
1180 evo_mthd(push, 0x0440 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 4);
1181 evo_data(push, 0x83000000);
1182 evo_data(push, nv_crtc->lut.nvbo->bo.offset >> 8);
1183 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
1184 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
1185 evo_mthd(push, 0x045c + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
1186 evo_data(push, mast->base.vram.handle);
1187 evo_mthd(push, 0x0430 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
1188 evo_data(push, 0xffffff00);
1189 }
1190
1191 evo_kick(push, mast);
1192 }
1193
1194 nv50_crtc_cursor_show_hide(nv_crtc, true, true);
1195 nv50_display_flip_next(crtc, crtc->primary->fb, NULL, 1);
1196}

1223static int
1224nv50_crtc_mode_set(struct drm_crtc *crtc, struct drm_display_mode *umode,
1225 struct drm_display_mode *mode, int x, int y,
1226 struct drm_framebuffer *old_fb)
1227{
1228 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(crtc->dev);
1229 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(crtc);
1230 struct nouveau_connector *nv_connector __unused;
1231 u32 ilace = (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE) ? 2 : 1;
1232 u32 vscan = (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_DBLSCAN) ? 2 : 1;
1233 u32 hactive, hsynce, hbackp, hfrontp, hblanke, hblanks;
1234 u32 vactive, vsynce, vbackp, vfrontp, vblanke, vblanks;
1235 u32 vblan2e = 0, vblan2s = 1, vblankus = 0;
1236 u32 *push;
1237 int ret;
1238
1239 hactive = mode->htotal;
1240 hsynce = mode->hsync_end - mode->hsync_start - 1;
1241 hbackp = mode->htotal - mode->hsync_end;
1242 hblanke = hsynce + hbackp;
1243 hfrontp = mode->hsync_start - mode->hdisplay;
1244 hblanks = mode->htotal - hfrontp - 1;
1245
1246 vactive = mode->vtotal * vscan / ilace;
1247 vsynce = ((mode->vsync_end - mode->vsync_start) * vscan / ilace) - 1;
1248 vbackp = (mode->vtotal - mode->vsync_end) * vscan / ilace;
1249 vblanke = vsynce + vbackp;
1250 vfrontp = (mode->vsync_start - mode->vdisplay) * vscan / ilace;
1251 vblanks = vactive - vfrontp - 1;
1252 /* XXX: Safe underestimate, even "0" works */
1253 vblankus = (vactive - mode->vdisplay - 2) * hactive;
1254 vblankus *= 1000;
1255 vblankus /= mode->clock;
1256
1257 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE) {
1258 vblan2e = vactive + vsynce + vbackp;
1259 vblan2s = vblan2e + (mode->vdisplay * vscan / ilace);
1260 vactive = (vactive * 2) + 1;
1261 }
1262
1263 ret = nv50_crtc_swap_fbs(crtc, old_fb);
1264 if (ret)
1265 return ret;
1266
1267 push = evo_wait(mast, 64);
1268 if (push) {
1269 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
1270 evo_mthd(push, 0x0804 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 2);
1271 evo_data(push, 0x00800000 | mode->clock);
1272 evo_data(push, (ilace == 2) ? 2 : 0);
1273 evo_mthd(push, 0x0810 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 6);
1274 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
1275 evo_data(push, (vactive << 16) | hactive);
1276 evo_data(push, ( vsynce << 16) | hsynce);
1277 evo_data(push, (vblanke << 16) | hblanke);
1278 evo_data(push, (vblanks << 16) | hblanks);
1279 evo_data(push, (vblan2e << 16) | vblan2s);
1280 evo_mthd(push, 0x082c + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 1);
1281 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
1282 evo_mthd(push, 0x0900 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x400), 2);
1283 evo_data(push, 0x00000311);
1284 evo_data(push, 0x00000100);
1285 } else {
1286 evo_mthd(push, 0x0410 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 6);
1287 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
1288 evo_data(push, (vactive << 16) | hactive);
1289 evo_data(push, ( vsynce << 16) | hsynce);
1290 evo_data(push, (vblanke << 16) | hblanke);
1291 evo_data(push, (vblanks << 16) | hblanks);
1292 evo_data(push, (vblan2e << 16) | vblan2s);
1293 evo_mthd(push, 0x042c + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 1);
1294 evo_data(push, 0x00000000); /* ??? */
1295 evo_mthd(push, 0x0450 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 3);
1296 evo_data(push, mode->clock * 1000);
1297 evo_data(push, 0x00200000); /* ??? */
1298 evo_data(push, mode->clock * 1000);
1299 evo_mthd(push, 0x04d0 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 2);
1300 evo_data(push, 0x00000311);
1301 evo_data(push, 0x00000100);
1302 }
1303
1304 evo_kick(push, mast);
1305 }
1306
1307 nv_connector = nouveau_crtc_connector_get(nv_crtc);
1308 nv50_crtc_set_dither(nv_crtc, false);
1309 nv50_crtc_set_scale(nv_crtc, false);
1310
1311 /* G94 only accepts this after setting scale */
1312 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA)
1313 nv50_crtc_set_raster_vblank_dmi(nv_crtc, vblankus);
1314
1315 nv50_crtc_set_color_vibrance(nv_crtc, false);
1316 nv50_crtc_set_image(nv_crtc, crtc->primary->fb, x, y, false);
1317 return 0;
1318}

1354static void
1355nv50_crtc_lut_load(struct drm_crtc *crtc)
1356{
1357 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(crtc->dev);
1358 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(crtc);
1359 void __iomem *lut = nvbo_kmap_obj_iovirtual(nv_crtc->lut.nvbo);
1360 int i;
1361
1362 for (i = 0; i < 256; i++) {
1363 u16 r = nv_crtc->lut.r[i] >> 2;
1364 u16 g = nv_crtc->lut.g[i] >> 2;
1365 u16 b = nv_crtc->lut.b[i] >> 2;
1366
1367 if (disp->disp->oclass < GF110_DISP) {
1368 writew(r + 0x0000, (char __iomem *)lut + (i * 0x08) + 0);
1369 writew(g + 0x0000, (char __iomem *)lut + (i * 0x08) + 2);
1370 writew(b + 0x0000, (char __iomem *)lut + (i * 0x08) + 4);
1371 } else {
1372 writew(r + 0x6000, (char __iomem *)lut + (i * 0x20) + 0);
1373 writew(g + 0x6000, (char __iomem *)lut + (i * 0x20) + 2);
1374 writew(b + 0x6000, (char __iomem *)lut + (i * 0x20) + 4);
1375 }
1376 }
1377}

1389static int
1390nv50_crtc_cursor_set(struct drm_crtc *crtc, struct drm_file *file_priv,
1391 uint32_t handle, uint32_t width, uint32_t height)
1392{
1393 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(crtc);
1394 struct drm_device *dev = crtc->dev;
1395 struct drm_gem_object *gem = NULL;
1396 struct nouveau_bo *nvbo = NULL;
1397 int ret = 0;
1398
1399 if (handle) {
1400 if (width != 64 || height != 64)
1401 return -EINVAL;
1402
1403 gem = drm_gem_object_lookup(dev, file_priv, handle);
1404 if (unlikely(!gem))
1405 return -ENOENT;
1406 nvbo = nouveau_gem_object(gem);
1407
1408 ret = nouveau_bo_pin(nvbo, TTM_PL_FLAG_VRAM, true);
1409 }
1410
1411 if (ret == 0) {
1412 if (nv_crtc->cursor.nvbo)
1413 nouveau_bo_unpin(nv_crtc->cursor.nvbo);
1414 nouveau_bo_ref(nvbo, &nv_crtc->cursor.nvbo);
1415 }
1416 drm_gem_object_unreference_unlocked(gem);
1417
1418 nv50_crtc_cursor_show_hide(nv_crtc, true, true);
1419 return ret;
1420}

1461static void
1462nv50_crtc_destroy(struct drm_crtc *crtc)
1463{
1464 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(crtc);
1465 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(crtc->dev);
1466 struct nv50_head *head = nv50_head(crtc);
1467 struct nv50_fbdma *fbdma;
1468
1469 list_for_each_entry(fbdma, &disp->fbdma, head) {
1470 nvif_object_fini(&fbdma->base[nv_crtc->index]);
1471 }
1472
1473 nv50_dmac_destroy(&head->ovly.base, disp->disp);
1474 nv50_pioc_destroy(&head->oimm.base);
1475 nv50_dmac_destroy(&head->sync.base, disp->disp);
1476 nv50_pioc_destroy(&head->curs.base);
1477
1478 /*XXX: this shouldn't be necessary, but the core doesn't call
1479 * disconnect() during the cleanup paths
1480 */
1481 if (head->image)
1482 nouveau_bo_unpin(head->image);
1483 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &head->image);
1484
1485 /*XXX: ditto */
1486 if (nv_crtc->cursor.nvbo)
1487 nouveau_bo_unpin(nv_crtc->cursor.nvbo);
1488 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &nv_crtc->cursor.nvbo);
1489
1490 nouveau_bo_unmap(nv_crtc->lut.nvbo);
1491 if (nv_crtc->lut.nvbo)
1492 nouveau_bo_unpin(nv_crtc->lut.nvbo);
1493 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &nv_crtc->lut.nvbo);
1494
1495 drm_crtc_cleanup(crtc);
1496 kfree(crtc);
1497}

1520static int
1521nv50_crtc_create(struct drm_device *dev, int index)
1522{
1523 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
1524 struct nvif_device *device = &drm->device;
1525 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(dev);
1526 struct nv50_head *head;
1527 struct drm_crtc *crtc;
1528 int ret, i;
1529
1530 head = kzalloc(sizeof(*head), GFP_KERNEL);
1531 if (!head)
1532 return -ENOMEM;
1533
1534 head->base.index = index;
1535 head->base.set_dither = nv50_crtc_set_dither;
1536 head->base.set_scale = nv50_crtc_set_scale;
1537 head->base.set_color_vibrance = nv50_crtc_set_color_vibrance;
1538 head->base.color_vibrance = 50;
1539 head->base.vibrant_hue = 0;
1540 head->base.cursor.set_pos = nv50_crtc_cursor_restore;
1541 for (i = 0; i < 256; i++) {
1542 head->base.lut.r[i] = i << 8;
1543 head->base.lut.g[i] = i << 8;
1544 head->base.lut.b[i] = i << 8;
1545 }
1546
1547 crtc = &head->base.base;
1548 drm_crtc_init(dev, crtc, &nv50_crtc_func);
1549 drm_crtc_helper_add(crtc, &nv50_crtc_hfunc);
1550 drm_mode_crtc_set_gamma_size(crtc, 256);
1551
1552 ret = nouveau_bo_new(dev, 8192, 0x100, TTM_PL_FLAG_VRAM,
1553 0, 0x0000, NULL, NULL, &head->base.lut.nvbo);
1554 if (!ret) {
1555 ret = nouveau_bo_pin(head->base.lut.nvbo, TTM_PL_FLAG_VRAM, true);
1556 if (!ret) {
1557 ret = nouveau_bo_map(head->base.lut.nvbo);
1558 if (ret)
1559 nouveau_bo_unpin(head->base.lut.nvbo);
1560 }
1561 if (ret)
1562 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &head->base.lut.nvbo);
1563 }
1564
1565 if (ret)
1566 goto out;
1567
1568 /* allocate cursor resources */
1569 ret = nv50_curs_create(device, disp->disp, index, &head->curs);
1570 if (ret)
1571 goto out;
1572
1573 /* allocate page flip / sync resources */
1574 ret = nv50_base_create(device, disp->disp, index, disp->sync->bo.offset,
1575 &head->sync);
1576 if (ret)
1577 goto out;
1578
1579 head->sync.addr = EVO_FLIP_SEM0(index);
1580 head->sync.data = 0x00000000;
1581
1582 /* allocate overlay resources */
1583 ret = nv50_oimm_create(device, disp->disp, index, &head->oimm);
1584 if (ret)
1585 goto out;
1586
1587 ret = nv50_ovly_create(device, disp->disp, index, disp->sync->bo.offset,
1588 &head->ovly);
1589 if (ret)
1590 goto out;
1591
1592out:
1593 if (ret)
1594 nv50_crtc_destroy(crtc);
1595 return ret;
1596}

1598/******************************************************************************
1599 * Encoder helpers
1600 *****************************************************************************/
1601static bool
1602nv50_encoder_mode_fixup(struct drm_encoder *encoder,
1603 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
1604 struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
1605{
1606 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
1607 struct nouveau_connector *nv_connector;
1608
1609 nv_connector = nouveau_encoder_connector_get(nv_encoder);
1610 if (nv_connector && nv_connector->native_mode) {
1611 nv_connector->scaling_full = false;
1612 if (nv_connector->scaling_mode == DRM_MODE_SCALE_NONE) {
1613 switch (nv_connector->type) {
1614 case DCB_CONNECTOR_LVDS:
1615 case DCB_CONNECTOR_LVDS_SPWG:
1616 case DCB_CONNECTOR_eDP:
1617 /* force use of scaler for non-edid modes */
1618 if (adjusted_mode->type & DRM_MODE_TYPE_DRIVER)
1619 return true;
1620 nv_connector->scaling_full = true;
1621 break;
1622 default:
1623 return true;
1624 }
1625 }
1626
1627 drm_mode_copy(adjusted_mode, nv_connector->native_mode);
1628 }
1629
1630 return true;
1631}

1634 * DAC
1635 *****************************************************************************/
1636static void
1637nv50_dac_dpms(struct drm_encoder *encoder, int mode)

1640 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(encoder->dev);

1646 .base.method = NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_DAC_PWR,
1647 .base.hasht = nv_encoder->dcb->hasht,
1648 .base.hashm = nv_encoder->dcb->hashm,
1649 .pwr.state = 1,
1650 .pwr.data = 1,
1651 .pwr.vsync = (mode != DRM_MODE_DPMS_SUSPEND &&
1652 mode != DRM_MODE_DPMS_OFF),
1653 .pwr.hsync = (mode != DRM_MODE_DPMS_STANDBY &&

1665static void
1666nv50_dac_mode_set(struct drm_encoder *encoder, struct drm_display_mode *mode,
1667 struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
1668{
1669 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(encoder->dev);
1670 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
1671 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(encoder->crtc);
1672 u32 *push;
1673
1674 nv50_dac_dpms(encoder, DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON);
1675
1676 push = evo_wait(mast, 8);
1677 if (push) {
1678 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
1679 u32 syncs = 0x00000000;
1680
1681 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC)
1682 syncs |= 0x00000001;
1683 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC)
1684 syncs |= 0x00000002;
1685
1686 evo_mthd(push, 0x0400 + (nv_encoder->or * 0x080), 2);
1687 evo_data(push, 1 << nv_crtc->index);
1688 evo_data(push, syncs);
1689 } else {
1690 u32 magic = 0x31ec6000 | (nv_crtc->index << 25);
1691 u32 syncs = 0x00000001;
1692
1693 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC)
1694 syncs |= 0x00000008;
1695 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC)
1696 syncs |= 0x00000010;
1697
1698 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE)
1699 magic |= 0x00000001;
1700
1701 evo_mthd(push, 0x0404 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 2);
1702 evo_data(push, syncs);
1703 evo_data(push, magic);
1704 evo_mthd(push, 0x0180 + (nv_encoder->or * 0x020), 1);
1705 evo_data(push, 1 << nv_crtc->index);
1706 }
1707
1708 evo_kick(push, mast);
1709 }
1710
1711 nv_encoder->crtc = encoder->crtc;
1712}

1714static void
1715nv50_dac_disconnect(struct drm_encoder *encoder)
1716{
1717 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
1718 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(encoder->dev);
1719 const int or = nv_encoder->or;
1720 u32 *push;
1721
1722 if (nv_encoder->crtc) {
1723 nv50_crtc_prepare(nv_encoder->crtc);
1724
1725 push = evo_wait(mast, 4);
1726 if (push) {
1727 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
1728 evo_mthd(push, 0x0400 + (or * 0x080), 1);
1729 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
1730 } else {
1731 evo_mthd(push, 0x0180 + (or * 0x020), 1);
1732 evo_data(push, 0x00000000);
1733 }
1734 evo_kick(push, mast);
1735 }
1736 }
1737
1738 nv_encoder->crtc = NULL;
1739}

1741static enum drm_connector_status
1742nv50_dac_detect(struct drm_encoder *encoder, struct drm_connector *connector)
1743{
1744 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
1745 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(encoder->dev);
1746 struct {

1753 .base.hashm = nv_encoder->dcb->hashm,

1755 int ret;

1790static int
1791nv50_dac_create(struct drm_connector *connector, struct dcb_output *dcbe)
1792{
1793 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(connector->dev);
1794 struct nvkm_i2c *i2c = nvxx_i2c(&drm->device);
1795 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus;
1796 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder;
1797 struct drm_encoder *encoder;
1798 int type = DRM_MODE_ENCODER_DAC;
1799
1800 nv_encoder = kzalloc(sizeof(*nv_encoder), GFP_KERNEL);
1801 if (!nv_encoder)
1802 return -ENOMEM;
1803 nv_encoder->dcb = dcbe;
1804 nv_encoder->or = ffs(dcbe->or) - 1;
1805

1935{
1936 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
1937 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(encoder->dev);
1938 struct {
1939 struct nv50_disp_mthd_v1 base;
1940 struct nv50_disp_sor_pwr_v0 pwr;
1941 } args = {
1942 .base.version = 1,

1944 .base.hasht = nv_encoder->dcb->hasht,
1945 .base.hashm = nv_encoder->dcb->hashm,
1946 .pwr.state = mode == DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON,
1947 };

1953 .base.method = NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_SOR_DP_PWR,
1954 .base.hasht = nv_encoder->dcb->hasht,
1955 .base.hashm = nv_encoder->dcb->hashm,
1956 .pwr.state = mode == DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON,
1957 };
1958 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;

1960
1961 nv_encoder->last_dpms = mode;
1962
1963 list_for_each_entry(partner, &dev->mode_config.encoder_list, head) {
1964 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_partner = nouveau_encoder(partner);
1965
1966 if (partner->encoder_type != DRM_MODE_ENCODER_TMDS)
1967 continue;
1968

1970 nv_partner->dcb->or == nv_encoder->dcb->or) {

1972 return;
1973 break;
1974 }
1975 }
1976
1977 if (nv_encoder->dcb->type == DCB_OUTPUT_DP) {
1978 args.pwr.state = 1;
1979 nvif_mthd(disp->disp, 0, &args, sizeof(args));
1980 nvif_mthd(disp->disp, 0, &link, sizeof(link));
1981 } else {
1982 nvif_mthd(disp->disp, 0, &args, sizeof(args));
1983 }
1984}

1986static void
1987nv50_sor_ctrl(struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder, u32 mask, u32 data)
1988{
1989 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(nv_encoder->base.base.dev);
1990 u32 temp = (nv_encoder->ctrl & ~mask) | (data & mask), *push;
1991 if (temp != nv_encoder->ctrl && (push = evo_wait(mast, 2))) {
1992 if (nv50_vers(mast) < GF110_DISP_CORE_CHANNEL_DMA) {
1993 evo_mthd(push, 0x0600 + (nv_encoder->or * 0x40), 1);
1994 evo_data(push, (nv_encoder->ctrl = temp));
1995 } else {
1996 evo_mthd(push, 0x0200 + (nv_encoder->or * 0x20), 1);
1997 evo_data(push, (nv_encoder->ctrl = temp));
1998 }
1999 evo_kick(push, mast);
2000 }
2001}

2025static void
2026nv50_sor_mode_set(struct drm_encoder *encoder, struct drm_display_mode *umode,
2027 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
2028{
2029 struct nouveau_encoder *nv_encoder = nouveau_encoder(encoder);
2030 struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(encoder->crtc);
2031 struct {
2032 struct nv50_disp_mthd_v1 base;
2033 struct nv50_disp_sor_lvds_script_v0 lvds;
2034 } lvds = {
2035 .base.version = 1,
2036 .base.method = NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_SOR_LVDS_SCRIPT,
2037 .base.hasht = nv_encoder->dcb->hasht,
2038 .base.hashm = nv_encoder->dcb->hashm,
2039 };
2040 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(encoder->dev);
2041 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(encoder->dev);
2042 struct drm_device *dev = encoder->dev;
2043 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
2044 struct nouveau_connector *nv_connector;
2045 struct nvbios *bios = &drm->vbios;
2046 u32 mask, ctrl;
2047 u8 owner = 1 << nv_crtc->index;
2048 u8 proto = 0xf;
2049 u8 depth = 0x0;
2050
2051 nv_connector = nouveau_encoder_connector_get(nv_encoder);
2052 nv_encoder->crtc = encoder->crtc;
2053
2054 switch (nv_encoder->dcb->type) {
2055 case DCB_OUTPUT_TMDS:
2056 if (nv_encoder->dcb->sorconf.link & 1) {
2057 if (mode->clock < 165000)
2058 proto = 0x1;
2059 else
2060 proto = 0x5;
2061 } else {
2062 proto = 0x2;
2063 }
2064
2065 nv50_hdmi_mode_set(&nv_encoder->base.base, mode);
2066 break;
2067 case DCB_OUTPUT_LVDS:
2068 proto = 0x0;
2069
2070 if (bios->fp_no_ddc) {
2071 if (bios->fp.dual_link)
2072 lvds.lvds.script |= 0x0100;
2073 if (bios->fp.if_is_24bit)
2074 lvds.lvds.script |= 0x0200;
2075 } else {
2076 if (nv_connector->type == DCB_CONNECTOR_LVDS_SPWG) {
2077 if (((u8 *)nv_connector->edid)[121] == 2)
2078 lvds.lvds.script |= 0x0100;
2079 } else
2080 if (mode->clock >= bios->fp.duallink_transition_clk) {
2081 lvds.lvds.script |= 0x0100;
2082 }
2083
2084 if (lvds.lvds.script & 0x0100) {
2085 if (bios->fp.strapless_is_24bit & 2)
2086 lvds.lvds.script |= 0x0200;
2087 } else {
2088 if (bios->fp.strapless_is_24bit & 1)
2089 lvds.lvds.script |= 0x0200;
2090 }
2091
2092 if (nv_connector->base.display_info.bpc == 8)
2093 lvds.lvds.script |= 0x0200;
2094 }
2095
2096 nvif_mthd(disp->disp, 0, &lvds, sizeof(lvds));
2097 break;
2098 case DCB_OUTPUT_DP:
2099 if (nv_connector->base.display_info.bpc == 6) {
2100 nv_encoder->dp.datarate = mode->clock * 18 / 8;
2101 depth = 0x2;
2102 } else
2103 if (nv_connector->base.display_info.bpc == 8) {
2104 nv_encoder->dp.datarate = mode->clock * 24 / 8;
2105 depth = 0x5;
2106 } else {
2107 nv_encoder->dp.datarate = mode->clock * 30 / 8;
2108 depth = 0x6;
2109 }
2110
2111 if (nv_encoder->dcb->sorconf.link & 1)
2112 proto = 0x8;
2113 else
2114 proto = 0x9;
2115 nv50_audio_mode_set(encoder, mode);
2116 break;
2117 default:
2118 BUG_ON(1);
2119 break;
2120 }
2121
2122 nv50_sor_dpms(&nv_encoder->base.base, DRM_MODE_DPMS_ON);
2123
2124 if (nv50_vers(mast) >= GF110_DISP) {
2125 u32 *push = evo_wait(mast, 3);
2126 if (push) {
2127 u32 magic = 0x31ec6000 | (nv_crtc->index << 25);
2128 u32 syncs = 0x00000001;
2129
2130 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC)
2131 syncs |= 0x00000008;
2132 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC)
2133 syncs |= 0x00000010;
2134
2135 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE)
2136 magic |= 0x00000001;
2137
2138 evo_mthd(push, 0x0404 + (nv_crtc->index * 0x300), 2);
2139 evo_data(push, syncs | (depth << 6));
2140 evo_data(push, magic);
2141 evo_kick(push, mast);
2142 }
2143
2144 ctrl = proto << 8;
2145 mask = 0x00000f00;
2146 } else {
2147 ctrl = (depth << 16) | (proto << 8);
2148 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC)
2149 ctrl |= 0x00001000;
2150 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC)
2151 ctrl |= 0x00002000;
2152 mask = 0x000f3f00;
2153 }
2154
2155 nv50_sor_ctrl(nv_encoder, mask | owner, ctrl | owner);
2156}

2424nv50_fbdma_init(struct drm_device *dev, u32 name, u64 offset, u64 length, u8 kind)
2425{
2426 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
2427 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(dev);
2428 struct nv50_mast *mast = nv50_mast(dev);
2429 struct __attribute__ ((packed)) {
2430 struct nv_dma_v0 base;
2431 union {
2432 struct nv50_dma_v0 nv50;
2433 struct gf100_dma_v0 gf100;
2434 struct gf119_dma_v0 gf119;
2435 };
2436 } args = {};
2437 struct nv50_fbdma *fbdma;
2438 struct drm_crtc *crtc;
2439 u32 size = sizeof(args.base);
2440 int ret;
2441
2442 list_for_each_entry(fbdma, &disp->fbdma, head) {
2443 if (fbdma->core.handle == name)
2444 return 0;
2445 }
2446
2447 fbdma = kzalloc(sizeof(*fbdma), GFP_KERNEL);
2448 if (!fbdma)
2449 return -ENOMEM;
2450 list_add(&fbdma->head, &disp->fbdma);
2451
2452 args.base.target = NV_DMA_V0_TARGET_VRAM;
2453 args.base.access = NV_DMA_V0_ACCESS_RDWR;
2454 args.base.start = offset;
2455 args.base.limit = offset + length - 1;
2456
2457 if (drm->device.info.chipset < 0x80) {
2458 args.nv50.part = NV50_DMA_V0_PART_256;
2459 size += sizeof(args.nv50);
2460 } else
2461 if (drm->device.info.chipset < 0xc0) {
2462 args.nv50.part = NV50_DMA_V0_PART_256;
2463 args.nv50.kind = kind;
2464 size += sizeof(args.nv50);
2465 } else
2466 if (drm->device.info.chipset < 0xd0) {
2467 args.gf100.kind = kind;
2468 size += sizeof(args.gf100);
2469 } else {
2470 args.gf119.page = GF119_DMA_V0_PAGE_LP;
2471 args.gf119.kind = kind;
2472 size += sizeof(args.gf119);
2473 }
2474
2475 list_for_each_entry(crtc, &dev->mode_config.crtc_list, head) {
2476 struct nv50_head *head = nv50_head(crtc);
2477 int ret = nvif_object_init(&head->sync.base.base.user, name,
2478 NV_DMA_IN_MEMORY, &args, size,
2479 &fbdma->base[head->base.index]);
2480 if (ret) {
2481 nv50_fbdma_fini(fbdma);
2482 return ret;
2483 }
2484 }
2485
2486 ret = nvif_object_init(&mast->base.base.user, name, NV_DMA_IN_MEMORY,
2487 &args, size, &fbdma->core);
2488 if (ret) {
2489 nv50_fbdma_fini(fbdma);
2490 return ret;
2491 }
2492
2493 return 0;
2494}

2500
2501static int
2502nv50_fb_ctor(struct drm_framebuffer *fb)
2503{
2504 struct nouveau_framebuffer *nv_fb = nouveau_framebuffer(fb);
2505 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(fb->dev);
2506 struct nouveau_bo *nvbo = nv_fb->nvbo;
2507 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(fb->dev);
2508 u8 kind = nouveau_bo_tile_layout(nvbo) >> 8;
2509 u8 tile = nvbo->tile_mode;
2510
2511 if (drm->device.info.chipset >= 0xc0)
2512 tile >>= 4; /* yep.. */
2513
2514 switch (fb->depth) {
2515 case 8: nv_fb->r_format = 0x1e00; break;
2516 case 15: nv_fb->r_format = 0xe900; break;
2517 case 16: nv_fb->r_format = 0xe800; break;
2518 case 24:
2519 case 32: nv_fb->r_format = 0xcf00; break;
2520 case 30: nv_fb->r_format = 0xd100; break;
2521 default:
2522 NV_ERROR(drm, "unknown depth %d\n", fb->depth);
2523 return -EINVAL;
2524 }
2525
2526 if (disp->disp->oclass < G82_DISP) {
2527 nv_fb->r_pitch = kind ? (((fb->pitches[0] / 4) << 4) | tile) :
2528 (fb->pitches[0] | 0x00100000);
2529 nv_fb->r_format |= kind << 16;
2530 } else
2531 if (disp->disp->oclass < GF110_DISP) {
2532 nv_fb->r_pitch = kind ? (((fb->pitches[0] / 4) << 4) | tile) :
2533 (fb->pitches[0] | 0x00100000);
2534 } else {
2535 nv_fb->r_pitch = kind ? (((fb->pitches[0] / 4) << 4) | tile) :
2536 (fb->pitches[0] | 0x01000000);
2537 }
2538 nv_fb->r_handle = 0xffff0000 | kind;
2539
2540 return nv50_fbdma_init(fb->dev, nv_fb->r_handle, 0,
2541 drm->device.info.ram_user, kind);
2542}

2553int
2554nv50_display_init(struct drm_device *dev)
2555{
2556 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(dev);
2557 struct drm_crtc *crtc;
2558 u32 *push;
2559
2560 push = evo_wait(nv50_mast(dev), 32);
2561 if (!push)
2562 return -EBUSY;
2563
2564 list_for_each_entry(crtc, &dev->mode_config.crtc_list, head) {
2565 struct nv50_sync *sync = nv50_sync(crtc);
2566
2567 nv50_crtc_lut_load(crtc);
2568 nouveau_bo_wr32(disp->sync, sync->addr / 4, sync->data);
2569 }
2570
2571 evo_mthd(push, 0x0088, 1);
2572 evo_data(push, nv50_mast(dev)->base.sync.handle);
2573 evo_kick(push, nv50_mast(dev));
2574 return 0;
2575}

2577void
2578nv50_display_destroy(struct drm_device *dev)
2579{
2580 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(dev);
2581 struct nv50_fbdma *fbdma, *fbtmp;
2582
2583 list_for_each_entry_safe(fbdma, fbtmp, &disp->fbdma, head) {
2584 nv50_fbdma_fini(fbdma);
2585 }
2586
2587 nv50_dmac_destroy(&disp->mast.base, disp->disp);
2588
2589 nouveau_bo_unmap(disp->sync);
2590 if (disp->sync)
2591 nouveau_bo_unpin(disp->sync);
2592 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &disp->sync);
2593
2594 nouveau_display(dev)->priv = NULL;
2595 kfree(disp);

2598int
2599nv50_display_create(struct drm_device *dev)
2600{
2601 struct nvif_device *device = &nouveau_drm(dev)->device;
2602 struct nouveau_drm *drm = nouveau_drm(dev);
2603 struct dcb_table *dcb = &drm->vbios.dcb;
2604 struct drm_connector *connector, *tmp;
2605 struct nv50_disp *disp;
2606 struct dcb_output *dcbe;
2607 int crtcs, ret, i;
2608
2609 disp = kzalloc(sizeof(*disp), GFP_KERNEL);
2610 if (!disp)
2611 return -ENOMEM;
2612 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&disp->fbdma);
2613
2614 nouveau_display(dev)->priv = disp;
2615 nouveau_display(dev)->dtor = nv50_display_destroy;
2616 nouveau_display(dev)->init = nv50_display_init;
2617 nouveau_display(dev)->fini = nv50_display_fini;
2618 nouveau_display(dev)->fb_ctor = nv50_fb_ctor;
2619 nouveau_display(dev)->fb_dtor = nv50_fb_dtor;
2620 disp->disp = &nouveau_display(dev)->disp;
2621
2622 /* small shared memory area we use for notifiers and semaphores */
2623 ret = nouveau_bo_new(dev, 4096, 0x1000, TTM_PL_FLAG_VRAM,
2624 0, 0x0000, NULL, NULL, &disp->sync);
2625 if (!ret) {
2626 ret = nouveau_bo_pin(disp->sync, TTM_PL_FLAG_VRAM, true);
2627 if (!ret) {
2628 ret = nouveau_bo_map(disp->sync);
2629 if (ret)
2630 nouveau_bo_unpin(disp->sync);
2631 }
2632 if (ret)
2633 nouveau_bo_ref(NULL, &disp->sync);
2634 }
2635
2636 if (ret)
2637 goto out;
2638
2639 /* allocate master evo channel */
2640 ret = nv50_core_create(device, disp->disp, disp->sync->bo.offset,
2641 &disp->mast);
2642 if (ret)
2643 goto out;
2644
2645 /* create crtc objects to represent the hw heads */
2646 if (disp->disp->oclass >= GF110_DISP)
2647 crtcs = nvif_rd32(&device->object, 0x022448);
2648 else
2649 crtcs = 2;
2650
2651 for (i = 0; i < crtcs; i++) {
2652 ret = nv50_crtc_create(dev, i);
2653 if (ret)
2654 goto out;
2655 }
2656
2657 /* create encoder/connector objects based on VBIOS DCB table */
2658 for (i = 0, dcbe = &dcb->entry[0]; i < dcb->entries; i++, dcbe++) {
2659 connector = nouveau_connector_create(dev, dcbe->connector);
2660 if (IS_ERR(connector))
2661 continue;
2662
2663 if (dcbe->location == DCB_LOC_ON_CHIP) {
2664 switch (dcbe->type) {
2665 case DCB_OUTPUT_TMDS:
2666 case DCB_OUTPUT_LVDS:
2667 case DCB_OUTPUT_DP:
2668 ret = nv50_sor_create(connector, dcbe);
2669 break;
2670 case DCB_OUTPUT_ANALOG:
2671 ret = nv50_dac_create(connector, dcbe);
2672 break;
2673 default:
2674 ret = -ENODEV;
2675 break;
2676 }
2677 } else {
2678 ret = nv50_pior_create(connector, dcbe);
2679 }
2680
2681 if (ret) {
2682 NV_WARN(drm, "failed to create encoder %d/%d/%d: %d\n",
2683 dcbe->location, dcbe->type,
2684 ffs(dcbe->or) - 1, ret);
2685 ret = 0;
2686 }
2687 }
2688
2689 /* cull any connectors we created that don't have an encoder */
2690 list_for_each_entry_safe(connector, tmp, &dev->mode_config.connector_list, head) {
2691 if (connector->encoder_ids[0])
2692 continue;
2693
2694 NV_WARN(drm, "%s has no encoders, removing\n",
2695 connector->name);
2696 connector->funcs->destroy(connector);
2697 }
2698
2699out:
2700 if (ret)
2701 nv50_display_destroy(dev);
2702 return ret;
2703}
